Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to
425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Trim and
thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}.
Mince @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

Toss carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon};
season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, spread carrots out across entire baking sheet.

Roast on top rack for ~{12%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

While carrots roast, in a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water
(11⁄2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil; cover and reduce to a
low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until
ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add salmon; sear, turning
occasionally, until browned all over, ~{5-7%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Once carrots have roasted 12 minutes, carefully add seared salmon to empty side of
baking sheet; wipe out pan. (For 4 servings, leave carrots roasting and add salmon to a
second baking sheet; roast on middle rack.) Return to top rack until carrots are
browned and tender and salmon is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Remove from oven; let salmon rest on baking sheet for ~{5%minutes}. Sprinkle carrots
with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}.

Heat half the @sesame oil{1%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings) and @butter{1/2%tbsp} in
same pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and half the ginger (add more if
desired). Cook until fragrant and softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @hot honey{1/2%ounce}, and 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup
for 4). Bring to a simmer; cook until slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat.

Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4); season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in cilantro, lime zest, juice from half the lime, and
@butter{1/2%tbsp} (1 TBSP for 4). Season with salt and pepper.

Stir in scallion greens and any resting juices from salmon to pan with sauce.

Slice salmon crosswise.

> Swap in chicken for pork: Cook until chicken is cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side
> (skip slicing salmon!).

Divide salmon, rice, and carrots between plates. Spoon sauce over salmon and serve with
remaining lime wedges on the side.